o
> have left the roles I have their cards from... do you have a scheme for
> this?
>

More of an anti-scheme. Just like I quit using folders for email (and now
use search) I'd suggest storing them in as accessible a data store as
possible. I don't have a good one, so am running my current media campaign
to self-sort. For example, I'm speaking to the head of UNICEF today, on
accident, but if it turns out she's too important or unpleasant then I'll
have to find a way to re-ingratiate myself later. In the meantime, there's
potential immediate value, and I'll know if it's worth moving her up a rung
in my contact circles.


>   * What is the "template" for doing reachouts? Does it make sense to use
> a sales funnel approach?
>

Absolutely, esp. because this allows for multivariate testing. Thoughts?

- J

